SUMMARY:Kickstart Your Lawn
DESCRIPTION:Join us and learn everything you need to know to kickstart your lawn this Spring!\n\n\nKick-start your growing season with this practical lawn and garden workshop. Learn how to create a healthier yard by making space for native plants\, choosing the right species\, and reducing paved areas. Discover how to assess your site\, understand sun exposure and soil types\, identify and remove invasive plants\, and improve lawn care through proper nutrition\, aeration\, mowing\, and watering. The workshop also introduces the basics of composting and rain barrel use\, giving you the tools to build a thriving\, more sustainable outdoor space \nYou will leave this workshop with a plan for a healthy\, beautiful yard! \nSaturday\, March 28 from 10 to 11:30 a.m. \nRegistration: Public $20\, TBG Members $15 (plus applicable taxes and fees) \nAbout Toronto and Region Conservation Authority (TRCA) \nToronto and Region Conservation Authority (TRCA) is one of 36 Conservation Authorities in Ontario. They: \n\nTake care of nine watersheds and the Lake Ontario shoreline\, in partnership with municipalities\, the Province\, and community members\,\nWork to preserve and protect the land\,\nMonitor and report on the health of the environment in the Toronto Region\,\nEngage communities and encourage people of all ages to get outside and enjoy nature!\n\nJoin Toronto Botanical Garden \nJoin the Toronto Botanical Garden (TBG) as a member to get a discount on this program\, upcoming events and classes\, and free parking. A TBG membership helps you deepen your knowledge and connection to the natural world\, become a part of a dynamic community of plant people\, and be inspired! Become a member! \nAdditional Program Information \n\nPlease review our Refund Policy and Terms of Agreement.\nFor more information on accessibility at the garden please review our Accessibility Features webpage. If you have any accessibility requirements during your program please email programsupport@torontobotanicalgarden.ca.\nTo learn more about the Toronto Botanical Garden and our programs\, please review our list of Frequently Asked Questions.
URL:https://torontobotanicalgarden.ca/event/kickstart-your-lawn/
LOCATION:Toronto Botanical Garden\, 777 Lawrence Avenue East\, Toronto\, ON\, M3C 1P2\, Canada
CATEGORIES:Gardening
