SUMMARY:Petal to Paper: Paper Cherry Blossom Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Join us to create lifelike paper cherry blossoms with botanical accuracy!Beautiful Cherry Blossoms arrive in early Spring but to our dismay the blooms are so short. Join paper artist Nancy Lalicon for the “Paper to Petal: Cherry Blossoms Workshop” to create your own bouquet of flowers which will last much\, much longer. In this 4-hour session\, participants will learn to create lifelike Cherry Blossoms in two shades of pink. Nancy will guide you through constructing the flowers using precut petals and leaf templates. You will have the opportunity to make as many branches as you wish. Discover the art of paper floristry and leave with your own stunning creations. Optional Items To Bring: Vase to keep your floral creation inSharp scissors (4”-5”)Preferred tools such as long nose pliers or wire cuttersAdditional colouring materialsTuesday\, April 14 from 10 a.m. to 2:30 p.m. There will be a 30-minute break for lunch. We recommend bringing a lunch as there are limited options nearby. Public $67\, TBG Members $57 (plus applicable taxes and fees) About Nancy Lalicon Nancy Lalicon is a multi-media sculptor specialized in making botanically accurate paper flowers and plants\, and in facilitating workshops for for community art organizations and local groups around Toronto and the GTA. From Peonies to Jupiter’s Beard to the Blazing Star\, Nancy has mastered the intricate art of creating environmentally friendly paper replicas; a modern day\, three dimensional take on botanical drawing. Trained in the Fine Arts at the University of Victoria and the Emily Carr College of Art in BC\, she received an MFA from Concordia University\, Montreal. Nancy lives in East Toronto with a large family who lovingly tolerate all her studio hours and mountains of flowers and roots.  Join Toronto Botanical GardenJoin the Toronto Botanical Garden (TBG) as a member to get a discount on this program\, upcoming events and classes\, and free parking. A TBG membership helps you deepen your knowledge and connection to the natural world\, become a part of a dynamic community of plant people\, and be inspired! Become a member!  Additional Program InformationPlease review our Refund Policy and Terms of Agreement.For more information on accessibility at the garden please review our Accessibility Features webpage. If you have any accessibility requirements during your program please email programsupport@torontobotanicalgarden.ca.To learn more about the Toronto Botanical Garden and our programs\, please review our list of Frequently Asked Questions.
URL:https://torontobotanicalgarden.ca/event/petal-to-paper-paper-cherry-blossom-workshop/
