SUMMARY:Paper Quilling: Lily of the Valley Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Join us this Mother’s Day for a fun-filled workshop on paper quilling and learn how to make amazing art with paper strips! Celebrate Mother’s Day with a touch of creativity and charm! In this beginner‑friendly workshop\, we’ll transform simple paper strips into delicate Lily of the Valley bells on a 5″x7″ canvas.\n \nNo prior experience needed – just bring your curiosity! The best part is you get to choose a vibrant color for the background and arrange the flowers in your own style\, making your heartfelt piece completely unique. Whether it’s a gift for mom or a keepsake for yourself\, this workshop is all about joy\, relaxation\, and crafting something beautiful together. Suitable for ages 12+.\n \nSunday\, May 10\, 2 to 4 p.m.Public $50\, TBG Members $45 (plus applicable taxes and fees).\n \nAbout Deepa Krishnan\nDeepa Krishnan is a self-taught artist specializing in the art of Paper Quilling which involves manipulating narrow strips of paper to create exquisite designs. She discovered this art form when she was looking for a creative outlet from her engineering job. She was amazed by the possibilities and beauty of paper quilling\, that she decided to pursue it as a full-time career. Since then\, she has been passionately mastering this technique and has created many artworks drawing inspiration from nature\, music and travel. She cuts the paper strips in different widths to add depth and dimension to her creations. She loves to play with the colours and experiment with the quilling techniques to create her own distinctive style. Deepa believes that anyone can learn this art form\, regardless of their age or skill level and she hosts many workshops to spread the joy of quilling. She enjoys seeing her students discover their own creativity and style in paper quilling. \nWebsite: https://www.deepakrishnan.com/ \n\n\nJoin Toronto Botanical Garden\nJoin the Toronto Botanical Garden (TBG) as a member to get a discount on this program\, upcoming events and classes\, and free parking. A TBG membership helps you deepen your knowledge and connection to the natural world\, become a part of a dynamic community of plant people\, and be inspired! Become a member! \nAdditional Program Information\n\nPlease review our Refund Policy and Terms of Agreement.\nFor more information on accessibility at the garden please review our Accessibility Features webpage. If you have any accessibility requirements during your program please email programsupport@torontobotanicalgarden.ca.\nTo learn more about the Toronto Botanical Garden and our programs\, please review our list of Frequently Asked Questions.
URL:https://torontobotanicalgarden.ca/event/paper-quilling-lily-of-the-valley-workshop/
LOCATION:Toronto Botanical Garden\, 777 Lawrence Avenue East\, Toronto\, ON\, M3C 1P2\, Canada
