SUMMARY:Summer Container Gardening: Plan with Purpose
DESCRIPTION:Jump into the spring\, summer\, and fall seasons\, harnessing your creative energies to create the container garden of your dreams!\n \nThis lecture is for those who have countless cell packs\, 4-inchers\, long-ago-divided perennials\, starts that never got planted\, and miscellaneous annuals you couldn’t say no to at the garden centre sale. Join Jess Conley\, TBG Horticulturist\, as she maps out strategies you can utilize on your ever-growing collection of pots and plants.\n \nLearn how to visually streamline your mess of pots into a cohesive\, well-considered statement piece and turn it into its latest metamorphosis\, a must-see feature of your garden.\n \nApply the lecture’s ideology to your plant hoard and make your new pot garden shine! Most important of all\, have your pot garden function as a cohesive whole!\n \nWednesday\, May 13\, 6 to 7:30 p.mPublic $20\, TBG Members $15 (plus applicable taxes and fees).\n \nAbout Jess Conley\nJess Conley is a botanic jack-of-all-trades. She’s been a tree planter\, a florist\, an urban farmer\, and an estate gardener. She studied Landscape Design\, but she found her joy in tending life. One of her specialties\, amongst many\, is edible flowers. However\, her palate is not limited to just flowers\, she can often be found on the grounds sampling horticultural treasures such as maple samaras and paw-paw fruit.\n \nJoin Toronto Botanical Garden\n \nJoin the Toronto Botanical Garden (TBG) as a member to get a discount on this program\, upcoming events and classes\, and free parking. A TBG membership helps you deepen your knowledge and connection to the natural world\, become a part of a dynamic community of plant people\, and be inspired! Become a member!\n \nAdditional Program Information\n\n\n\nPlease review our Refund Policy and Terms of Agreement.\nFor more information on accessibility at the garden please review our Accessibility Features webpage. If you have any accessibility requirements during your program please email programsupport@torontobotanicalgarden.ca.\nTo learn more about the Toronto Botanical Garden and our programs\, please review our list of Frequently Asked Questions.
URL:https://torontobotanicalgarden.ca/event/summer-container-gardening-plan-with-purpose/
