SUMMARY:Toronto Botanical Garden Spring Plant Sale 2026
DESCRIPTION:Every spring\, the Toronto Botanical Garden comes alive with one of the most anticipated events of the season\, our Spring Plant Sale from May 22 through 24\, 2026. Enjoy a friendly and relaxed shopping experience surrounded by plants and the people who care for them. It’s more than a plant sale. It’s where the community comes to share the benefits of connecting with nature and one another.  \n\n\n\nWhat Makes the TBG Spring Plant Sale So Special:\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nShop for Expert-Curated Plants \n\n\n\nOur plants are carefully selected for Toronto’s growing conditions that are hardy\, beautiful\, pollinator-friendly\, and garden-tested. You’ll find unique annuals and perennials\, native plants that support local biodiversity and hard-to-find varieties you won’t see elsewhere.  \n\n\n\nOpen to the PublicMay 23 and 24 from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nTBGs Member Shop First\n\n\n\nWhen you become a member of the Garden\, you receive early access to the Spring Plant Sale\, giving you first pick of the most sought-after varieties before doors open to the general public. In addition\, you’ll become part of a vibrant gardening community that connects people with plants all year long \n\n\n\nTBG Members Plant Sale PreviewFriday\, May 22\, 1 to 7 p.m. \n\n\n\nNot a member? Join Today! \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nVisit the Garden Shop\n\n\n\nThe TBG Garden Shop is open all year long and during spring it’s especially stocked and ready for the start of gardening. \n\n\n\nMembers receive exclusive discounts. Open daily from 10:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFree Advice from Toronto Master Gardeners\n\n\n\nHave questions? Bring them! Knowledgeable volunteers from the Toronto Master Gardeners are onsite to offer free\, practical advice — from soil prep and plant selection to pest issues and small-space gardening tips. It’s like having a garden coach by your side. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nNEW: Order & Ship Directly to Your Home\n\n\n\nVisit our new Plant Order Kiosk to browse expanded selections and order plants to be shipped directly to your home. It’s convenience meets inspiration and is an option for on-demand plant shopping. \n\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBorrow from Our Free Seed Library\n\n\n\nTry something new this season. Browse and borrow seeds from our community Seed Library — a wonderful way to experiment with new varieties\, connect with fellow gardeners\, and participate in seed saving traditions. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMake a Day of It\n\n\n\nWhy rush? After shopping\, relax at the garden’s beloved café\, Dandelion Café\, for fresh\, seasonal fare and a coffee break surrounded by nature. Then browse our year-round Garden Shop for tools\, gifts\, books\, and beautiful botanical finds you won’t discover anywhere else. \n\n\n\nStroll the gardens. Visit the ravine. Let inspiration strike. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSpecialty Plant Vendors\n\n\n\nThis year\, we’re welcoming a curated lineup of specialty plant vendors offering unique and hard-to-find varieties. More details coming soon. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nTIPS AND SUGGESTIONS\n\n\n\n\nIf you have old plant trays\, bins\, or cardboard trays\, bring them to gather and safely transport your plants home. We would be happy to accept donations of old plant trays too!\n\n\n\nWe have a limited supply of wagons and carts to gather your plants while shopping. If you have a wagon or cart you are welcome to bring it.\n\n\n\n\nAll proceeds support the Toronto Botanical Garden.
URL:https://torontobotanicalgarden.ca/event/toronto-botanical-garden-spring-plant-sale-2026/
LOCATION:ON
CATEGORIES:Plantapalooza
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://torontobotanicalgarden.ca/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/TBG-Plant-Sale-Danemark-Photographic-Art.jpg
